        "Subcategory": "Identity:public",
        "Description": "Leave blank for new deployments \u2014 the server will auto-derive a stable WorldName from your token and register it with Funcom on first start. **Funcom permanently binds that name to your token and provides no way to change it afterwards**, so the auto-derived value (logged prominently on first start) is your forever-identity for this self-host slot. Only fill this field if you previously bound a different WorldName under the same Self-Host Service Token (e.g. via Funcom\u2019s own self-host script) and need to reclaim that exact FLS slot \u2014 format: sh-<hex>-<suffix>.",
